  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  between 18 and 80 years of age (whereby for most studies the majority of recruited&#xD;
             participants will be between 18 and 40 years of age)&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  right-handedness and/or one specific gender (male or female) can be inclusion criteria&#xD;
             to reduce variation in the data.&#xD;
&#xD;
        Exclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  inability to understand the instructions and insufficient knowledge of the project&#xD;
             language&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Internal electronic and/or metallic objects in the head, neck, or shoulders (e.g.&#xD;
             artificial cochleae, deep brain stimulators, medical pumps, shrapnel, metallic&#xD;
             splinters due to accidents during metal welding)&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  One or more epileptic fits in the participant or a first-degree relative&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Vascular, traumatic, tumoral, infectious, or metabolic brain damage&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Use of medication that significantly alters cortical excitability&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  Acute sleep deprivation or withdrawal from alcohol&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  pregnancy&#xD;
&#xD;
          -  to reduce bias, students of psychology or economics can be excluded if there is a&#xD;
             possibility that they are familiar with the relevant paradigm.&#xD;
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
